    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1988-08-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1988-08-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="275"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d275">
                <head>275. Memorandum From the President’s Assistant for National Security Affairs
                        (<persName corresp="#p_PCL_1">Powell</persName>) to President <persName
                        corresp="#p_RRW_1">Reagan</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d275fn1">Source: National Security Council,
                        National Security Council Institutional Files, Box SR–097, <gloss
                            target="#t_NSDD_1">NSDD</gloss> 313. Secret. Sent for action. Prepared
                        by <persName corresp="#p_LR_2">Linhard</persName> and <persName
                            corresp="#p_HGW_1">Heiser</persName>. Copies were sent to <persName
                            corresp="#p_BGHW_1">Bush</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_DK_2"
                            >Duberstein</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1988-08-12">August 12, 1988</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_ABM_1">ABM</gloss> Treaty Review—Proposed <gloss
                            target="#t_NSDD_1">NSDD</gloss> on <gloss target="#t_US_1">U.S.</gloss>
                        Delegation Instructions</item>
                </list>
                <p rend="sectiontitleital">Issue</p>
                <p>Whether to sign the National Security Decision Directive providing instructions
                    to the <gloss target="#t_US_1">U.S.</gloss> Delegation to the <gloss
                        target="#t_ABM_1">ABM</gloss> Treaty Review which is scheduled to begin on
                    August 24, 1988.</p>
                <p rend="sectiontitleital">Background</p>
                <p>In <gloss target="#t_NSDD_1">NSDD</gloss>–312,<note n="2" xml:id="d275fn2">See
                            <ref target="#d272">Document 272</ref>.</note> you provided guidance to
                    agencies for the conduct of the Review and, <hi rend="italic">inter alia</hi>,
                    directed that the special interagency <gloss target="#t_ABM_1">ABM</gloss>
                    Treaty Review Steering Group should finalize and provide for your approval the
                        <gloss target="#t_US_1">U.S.</gloss> Delegation instructions and the plenary
                    statements to be tabled during the <gloss target="#t_ABM_1">ABM</gloss> Treaty
                    Review. In response to your directive, the Steering Group has forwarded these
                    documents for review and approval.</p>
                <p rend="sectiontitleital">Discussion</p>
                <p>The instructions to the Delegation in the proposed <gloss target="#t_NSDD_1"
                        >NSDD</gloss> at <hi rend="italic">Tab A</hi>
                    <note n="3" xml:id="d275fn3">Printed as <ref target="#d276">Document
                        276</ref>.</note> indicate that you have decided <hi rend="italic">not</hi>
                    to declare the illegal Soviet radar near Krasnoyarsk a material breach of the
                        <gloss target="#t_ABM_1">ABM</gloss> Treaty during the <gloss
                        target="#t_ABM_1">ABM</gloss> Treaty Review. The instructions make it clear
                    that the <gloss target="#t_US_1">U.S.</gloss> would consider such an action in
                    the future, but there is no suggestion that a decision has been made now to
                    declare a material breach after the Treaty Review. The instructions also call
                    for putting the Soviets on notice during the Treaty Review that should the
                    Soviet Union continue to refuse to correct the Krasnoyarsk radar violation, the
                        <gloss target="#t_US_1">U.S.</gloss> would reserve its rights to take the
                    appropriate proportionate response in the future, including a declaration of
                    material breach.</p>
                <pb facs="1014" n="983" xml:id="pg_983"/>
                <p>The plenary statements, unilateral <gloss target="#t_US_1">U.S.</gloss>
                    statement, communique and protocol at <hi rend="italic">Tab B</hi>
                    <note n="4" xml:id="d275fn4">Attached but not printed.</note> are fully
                    consistent with the attached <gloss target="#t_NSDD_1">NSDD</gloss> and
                    therefore may be forwarded to agencies along with the attached <gloss
                        target="#t_NSDD_1">NSDD</gloss>. They do not require your review.</p>
                <p>In accordance with <gloss target="#t_NSDD_1">NSDD</gloss>–266,<note n="5"
                        xml:id="d275fn5">
                        <gloss target="#t_NSDD_1">NSDD</gloss> 266, “Implementation of the
                        Recommendations of the President’s Special Review Board,” March 31, 1987, is
                        scheduled for publication in <ref target="frus1981-88v02">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1981–1988, vol. II,
                            Organization and Management of Foreign Policy</ref>.</note>
                    <persName corresp="#p_RN_1">Nicholas Rostow</persName>, Legal Adviser to the
                        <gloss target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss>, has coordinated the attached <gloss
                        target="#t_NSDD_1">NSDD</gloss> with A.B. Culvahouse in advance of its
                    submission to you.</p>
                <p rend="sectiontitleital">Recommendation</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">OK NO</hi>
                </p>
                <p>____ ____ That you sign the <gloss target="#t_NSDD_1">NSDD</gloss> at <hi
                        rend="italic">Tab A</hi>.<note n="6" xml:id="d275fn6">
                        <persName corresp="#p_RRW_1">Reagan</persName> approved the
                        recommendation.</note>
                </p>
            </div>
